    "custom_liquid_DmTYFc": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Repairs",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<style>\n/* ---------- WATCH REPAIR CATEGORIES ---------- */\n.repair-categories {\n  max-width: 950px;\n  margin: 0 auto 80px auto;\n}\n\n.repair-category {\n  background: #ebecf0;\n  border-radius: 12px;\n  padding: 35px;\n  margin-bottom: 30px;\n  border-left: 5px solid #111;\n}\n\n.repair-category h3 {\n  font-size: 26px;\n  margin-bottom: 14px;\n}\n\n.repair-category p,\n.repair-category li {\n  font-size: 16px;\n  line-height: 1.65;\n  color: #555;\n}\n\n.repair-link {\n  display: inline-block;\n  background:#111;\n  color:#fff !important;\n  padding: 12px 28px;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  margin-top: 14px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n}\n</style>\n\n<section id=\"repair-categories\" class=\"repair-categories\">\n\n<!-- DISPLAY (OLED) -->\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>Apple Watch Display (OLED) Repair</h3>\n<p>The Apple Watch OLED display is a sophisticated component that combines the touch-sensitive glass, OLED panel, and digitizer in a single assembly. When damaged, the entire display assembly requires replacement to restore your Apple Watch to full functionality.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Display issues we repair:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cracked or shattered display glass from impacts or drops</li>\n<li>OLED screen damage showing lines, dead pixels, or colour issues</li>\n<li>Completely black or unresponsive screen</li>\n<li>Touch functionality not working or registering incorrect inputs</li>\n<li>Display separation or lifting from the watch body</li>\n<li>Backlight issues or dim display</li>\n<li>Green line or other display artifacts</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We use genuine OLED displays that match original specifications for brightness, colour accuracy, and touch sensitivity. Our technicians carefully install the new display and test all functions including Force Touch, Digital Crown responsiveness, and display quality before returning your watch.</p>\n\nView Display Repair Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<!-- GLASS ONLY -->\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>Apple Watch Screen Glass Replacement</h3>\n<p>If your Apple Watch has surface cracks or scratches on the protective glass but the OLED display underneath is functioning normally, glass-only replacement may be a viable repair option, though this is highly dependent on the extent of damage and watch model.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Glass repair considerations:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Surface scratches and minor cracks that don't affect display function</li>\n<li>Sapphire crystal replacement for premium models (Stainless Steel, Titanium, Edition)</li>\n<li>Ion-X glass replacement for aluminium models</li>\n<li>Chipped or damaged edges of the protective glass</li>\n<li>Cracks that haven't penetrated to the OLED layer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It's important to note that due to the Apple Watch's integrated design, glass-only repairs aren't always possible. In many cases, especially with significant cracks or when the digitizer is affected, complete display assembly replacement is necessary. During our diagnostic, we'll assess your specific watch and recommend the most appropriate and cost-effective repair solution. For sapphire crystal models, we use genuine sapphire replacements to maintain the premium scratch resistance.</p>\n\nView Screen Glass Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<!-- BATTERY -->\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>Apple Watch Battery Replacement</h3>\n<p>Apple Watch batteries degrade over time, reducing battery life and device performance. If your Apple Watch no longer lasts through the day on a single charge, our battery replacement service restores full battery capacity and performance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Signs you need an Apple Watch battery replacement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Watch requires charging multiple times per day with normal use</li>\n<li>Battery drains rapidly even in low power mode</li>\n<li>Watch shuts down unexpectedly despite showing charge remaining</li>\n<li>Slow or inconsistent charging behaviour</li>\n<li>Watch only works when on the charger</li>\n<li>Swollen battery causing display lifting or back case separation</li>\n<li>Overheating during charging or regular wear</li>\n<li>Watch is 2–3+ years old and battery life has noticeably degraded</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Apple Watch battery replacement is a delicate procedure due to the compact design and adhesive securing the battery. Our technicians use specialised tools to safely remove the old battery without damaging other components, then install a gebnuine replacement battery. All battery replacements include proper re-sealing to maintain water resistance and comprehensive testing to ensure optimal performance and charging.</p>\n\nView Battery Replacement Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<!-- DIAGNOSTIC -->\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>Apple Watch Diagnostic Service</h3>\n<p>Not sure what's causing your Apple Watch issues? Our detailed diagnostic service identifies all hardware and software problems, providing you with a comprehensive assessment and transparent repair recommendations.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Our Apple Watch diagnostic service includes:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Complete hardware functionality testing (display, battery, sensors, buttons)</li>\n<li>Digital Crown and side button operation testing</li>\n<li>Taptic Engine (haptic feedback) evaluation</li>\n<li>Heart rate sensor, ECG, and blood oxygen sensor testing (where applicable)</li>\n<li>Charging system and wireless charging coil inspection</li>\n<li>Water damage assessment and moisture detection</li>\n<li>Bluetooth and Wi-Fi connectivity testing</li>\n<li>Detailed report with transparent pricing for required repairs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We explain all issues clearly and provide honest advice about whether repair is worthwhile or if replacement might be more economical. Whether your Apple Watch won't turn on, isn't charging, or is experiencing sensor problems, our diagnostic service identifies the exact cause and provides you with the information you need to make an informed decision.</p>\n\nView Diagnostic Service →\n</div>\n\n</section>",
